cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM

The paper deals with a new dataset that resembles the input to biological vision systems, and analyzes the possibility of disambiguating visual scenes encountered over the course of several weeks of a human life with high accuracy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the suitability of generative models such as Latent Dirichlet Allocation or Counting Grids, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The potential applications of the research, such as early detection of dementia and everyday use of wearable camera streams, suggest that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the focus on visual stream exchange suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
